  "commentary": "With SPX at 6857.74 sitting above the 6839 GEX flip and just below the massive 6850 gamma wall (7.8B), dealers are likely selling into this current level as they hedge their long gamma position. The PIN regime combined with the dense positive gamma structure from 6850-7000 creates a strong magnetic pull toward these strikes, with dealers providing liquidity by fading moves away from gamma-heavy levels. Key levels to watch are the 6839 flip below (where dealer behavior reverses) and the 6850/6900 gamma walls above that should act as speed bumps on any rally attempt.\n\nBottom line: expect choppy action with upside capped near 6850-6900 and support building above 6839.",
